WEBVTT

00:00:02.171 --> 00:00:04.843
[NARRATOR] Long before
the hero of Ente Isla

00:00:04.927 --> 00:00:07.389
-had taken her first breath.
-[grunts]

00:00:08.350 --> 00:00:12.107
Constant massacres
left the soil of the demon realm

00:00:12.191 --> 00:00:15.447
-under a blanket of crimson
blood. -[demons screech]

00:00:15.531 --> 00:00:17.869
After the ancient king's
demise,

00:00:17.953 --> 00:00:21.502
demonkind was left
without a unifying force.

00:00:21.585 --> 00:00:23.548
Living became surviving.

00:00:23.631 --> 00:00:26.679
In a lawless world
of fear and violence,

00:00:26.762 --> 00:00:29.392
they were left
without a choice.

00:00:29.475 --> 00:00:30.770
[LAILAH]
In my opinion...

00:00:31.479 --> 00:00:34.945
the idea there is one "paradise"
is rather suspect.

00:00:35.028 --> 00:00:36.489
Many might disagree,

00:00:36.573 --> 00:00:39.538
but I find the red
that paints this land beautiful.

00:00:39.621 --> 00:00:41.332
♪

00:00:41.416 --> 00:00:43.754
Ah. [gasping]

00:00:43.838 --> 00:00:46.760
[MAOU]
But red is so scary.

00:00:46.844 --> 00:00:50.810
Those lights. You fear
not the color they boldly paint?

00:00:50.893 --> 00:00:53.273
Would you like me to tell you
this color's name?

00:00:54.776 --> 00:00:55.820
Mm-hm.

00:00:56.362 --> 00:00:59.452
Then I shall teach you
about the world in full.

00:00:59.536 --> 00:01:01.707
This requires a willingness
to look past

00:01:01.790 --> 00:01:02.834
your aversion to red

00:01:02.917 --> 00:01:04.755
and see a different
side to the color.

00:01:09.347 --> 00:01:11.059
Tell me, what is your name?

00:01:11.727 --> 00:01:13.313
Satan.

00:01:13.396 --> 00:01:15.150
It suits you well.

00:01:15.233 --> 00:01:17.112
Prepare yourself
as I bestow the knowledge

00:01:17.446 --> 00:01:19.033
of the world unto you.

00:01:19.826 --> 00:01:21.245
Knowledge
that will empower you

00:01:21.329 --> 00:01:24.586
to find the beauty
in your once fear-clouded red.

00:01:31.057 --> 00:01:33.521
That color shining from above
is called...

00:01:37.444 --> 00:01:38.864
[MAOU]
This is freakin' sick!

00:01:38.948 --> 00:01:41.202
We're rocking
automatic faucets?

00:01:41.285 --> 00:01:45.545
No way. And we've gone tankless
in the toilet department?

00:01:45.628 --> 00:01:47.924
These bad boys
will be way easier to clean.

00:01:48.007 --> 00:01:49.928
-Plus a motion sensor?
-[sensor whirring]

00:01:50.555 --> 00:01:52.725
No more pissy lids
around here!

00:01:52.809 --> 00:01:55.272
The bathrooms are great,
but it just gets better.

00:01:55.355 --> 00:01:57.151
Don't waste
all your excitement.

00:01:57.234 --> 00:01:58.612
This ain't nothing!

00:01:58.696 --> 00:02:01.075
[KISAKI] The booths were
recovered in muted colors

00:02:01.159 --> 00:02:03.288
to evoke the look
of expensive leather.

00:02:03.371 --> 00:02:05.083
All the new furnishings
have a simpler,

00:02:05.167 --> 00:02:06.461
more understated look.

00:02:06.545 --> 00:02:08.465
We switched out
the old burger griddles

00:02:08.591 --> 00:02:09.634
for the latest model.

00:02:09.718 --> 00:02:11.847
And now, we have
three instead of two!

00:02:11.930 --> 00:02:15.813
And now, the pièce de resistance
the world's been waiting for:

00:02:15.897 --> 00:02:17.609
our second-floor café space.

00:02:17.692 --> 00:02:18.694
MgCafé!

00:02:19.069 --> 00:02:21.115
Happy place!

00:02:21.575 --> 00:02:23.621
It doesn't look
like MgR's at all!

00:02:23.704 --> 00:02:25.666
And I mean that in
a classy, good way!

00:02:25.750 --> 00:02:27.545
The space itself is
way more refined,

00:02:27.629 --> 00:02:30.091
but it still has that same,
chilled-out MgRonald's feeling!

00:02:30.175 --> 00:02:32.972
It's not fair that
you got to go see it without me!

00:02:33.056 --> 00:02:35.477
I'm still waiting
for a shift assignment.

00:02:35.561 --> 00:02:36.980
If you don't mind
my asking, Sire,

00:02:37.064 --> 00:02:39.611
what's the true difference
between this "MgCafé"

00:02:39.694 --> 00:02:40.988
and the standard MgRonald's?

00:02:41.072 --> 00:02:43.368
Come on. The answer
is right in the name.

00:02:43.451 --> 00:02:45.915
Coffee, and lots
of it! It's a ton.

00:02:45.998 --> 00:02:48.879
We've got café au lait,
latte, espressos.

00:02:48.963 --> 00:02:50.925
There'll be some
new snacks, too!

00:02:51.008 --> 00:02:52.929
Fancy café cakes and stuff!

00:02:53.012 --> 00:02:54.223
Whoa, intense.

00:02:54.306 --> 00:02:55.935
Could you remind me
of the difference between

00:02:56.018 --> 00:02:57.479
a café au lait
and a latte?

00:02:57.564 --> 00:02:59.776
Yeah, sure!
It's pretty simple.

00:02:59.860 --> 00:03:02.155
You see, café au laits
are loaded up with milk,

00:03:02.239 --> 00:03:05.746
and lattes are loaded up with...
Milk. Hey, wait a sec.

00:03:06.205 --> 00:03:08.586
So, they're both coffee-flavored
milk, how thrilling.

00:03:08.669 --> 00:03:09.796
[MAOU]
How dare you?

00:03:09.880 --> 00:03:11.090
You've got
no respect for the

00:03:11.173 --> 00:03:12.760
carefully
curated café vibe!

00:03:15.140 --> 00:03:16.392
Ah! You wretch!

00:03:16.475 --> 00:03:17.477
You know good and well

00:03:17.562 --> 00:03:19.733
that "he who finishes
always replenishes!"

00:03:19.816 --> 00:03:21.235
Lay off, Mom.

00:03:21.319 --> 00:03:23.364
There's still some tea left.

00:03:23.448 --> 00:03:25.870
Hey, yo. Haagen-Desse.

00:03:25.953 --> 00:03:28.374
That creamed ice
was a gift from Miss Sasaki!

00:03:28.458 --> 00:03:30.546
At least thank her
before you destroy it!

00:03:30.630 --> 00:03:32.090
And once you've
finished your treat,

00:03:32.174 --> 00:03:34.345
rinse the container prior
to throwing it away!

00:03:34.721 --> 00:03:36.474
Lest you want to attract more
Blattella germa--

00:03:36.558 --> 00:03:38.604
[EMI] Though they once fought
grand wars,

00:03:38.687 --> 00:03:41.985
now our petty demon generals
prefer tiny squabbles.

00:03:42.069 --> 00:03:44.866
Oh, great. Would it really kill
you to knock?

00:03:45.283 --> 00:03:47.789
Hi, Chi-mi! Dada!

00:03:47.872 --> 00:03:50.043
Hey there, Alas Ramus!

00:03:50.126 --> 00:03:52.464
We're going to borrow Chiho
for a while, okay?

00:03:52.507 --> 00:03:53.926
[MAOU] What do you mean
"borrow," creep?

00:03:54.009 --> 00:03:55.053
How curious.

00:03:55.136 --> 00:03:57.725
Didn't you spirit her off
somewhere yesterday, as well?

00:03:57.809 --> 00:04:00.146
It's known as "girl
talk". Fret not.

00:04:00.940 --> 00:04:03.654
Why don't you look for something
on TV to watch with the kiddo?

00:04:03.737 --> 00:04:06.075
-Dada!
-How goes it, short stack?

00:04:06.158 --> 00:04:08.454
Chi and the others
are gonna be busy for a bit.

00:04:08.539 --> 00:04:10.083
So you get to hang with me!

00:04:10.166 --> 00:04:11.335
[Alas, Emi chuckle]

00:04:12.003 --> 00:04:13.423
[door slams]

00:04:16.930 --> 00:04:19.936
♪

00:04:24.946 --> 00:04:27.952
I can't tell. Is Mister Maou
getting suspicious?

00:04:28.036 --> 00:04:30.498
I hate using Alas
Ramus as a decoy.

00:04:30.583 --> 00:04:33.589
But with a baby in his hands,
he won't notice anything else.

00:04:33.672 --> 00:04:35.008
Knowing the two of them,

00:04:35.091 --> 00:04:38.097
I fear Aliciel is the one
who will start asking questions.

00:04:38.557 --> 00:04:40.101
You'll pay for what you've done!

00:04:40.185 --> 00:04:41.688
Angy!

00:04:41.772 --> 00:04:44.109
Yeah, nice, he looks
angry for sure.

00:04:44.193 --> 00:04:45.529
Two days now.

00:04:45.613 --> 00:04:47.115
-Doesn't that strike you as odd?
-Hm?

00:04:47.199 --> 00:04:49.119
[MAOU]
Hm? What do you mean?

00:04:49.203 --> 00:04:50.413
Their "girl talks".

00:04:50.497 --> 00:04:52.417
They've had them two days
in a row now.

00:04:52.543 --> 00:04:53.587
Strange, yes?

00:04:53.670 --> 00:04:55.381
Hey, I'm not complaining.

00:04:55.465 --> 00:04:56.676
Whatever they're doing
in there,

00:04:56.760 --> 00:04:59.599
it means we get extra time
with Baby Smith Apple.

00:05:00.058 --> 00:05:02.980
They call it "talk," though
I suspect more than mere chat.

00:05:03.565 --> 00:05:06.571
♪

00:05:08.449 --> 00:05:09.493
Hm?

00:05:14.336 --> 00:05:16.382
[URUSHIHARA] Her heroic highness
will beat your ass

00:05:16.465 --> 00:05:18.427
if she finds out you
eavesdropped on them.

00:05:18.512 --> 00:05:20.306
Shh!

00:05:20.390 --> 00:05:21.225
Ah!

00:05:21.308 --> 00:05:22.477
Well, spill.

00:05:22.562 --> 00:05:24.899
It seems they're watching
Okorinbo, too.

00:05:24.983 --> 00:05:26.695
Intense choice of soundtrack.

00:05:26.778 --> 00:05:28.615
-Weird, huh?
-Silence!

00:05:28.699 --> 00:05:30.243
The "talk" has commenced.

00:05:30.326 --> 00:05:31.621
Bath.

00:05:31.705 --> 00:05:33.625
Blood bath? No choice?

00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:34.752
"Bloodbath?"

00:05:34.836 --> 00:05:36.715
Who the heck do they think
they're fighting?

00:05:36.798 --> 00:05:39.177
Before too long,
the frequency of our meetings

00:05:39.261 --> 00:05:41.223
will make it hard
to keep them in the dark.

00:05:41.307 --> 00:05:44.104
We should devise a cover story
while we still can.

00:05:44.689 --> 00:05:46.275
Who's in the dark?

00:05:46.358 --> 00:05:47.945
Cover story?

00:05:48.029 --> 00:05:49.866
What could they
be talking about?

00:05:49.949 --> 00:05:51.160
-[Alas giggles]
-Well, cutie,

00:05:51.243 --> 00:05:52.580
you heard anything juicy?

00:05:52.663 --> 00:05:55.418
[OKORINBO, ALAS] And prepare to
pay with your lives!

00:05:59.051 --> 00:06:00.512
They've exited the room.

00:06:00.596 --> 00:06:03.560
Bet they're taking their convo
to a restaurant or something.

00:06:03.644 --> 00:06:07.317
Chill. Whatever's going on,
no way Chi would betray us.

00:06:07.400 --> 00:06:08.946
Let 'em do their thing.

00:06:09.029 --> 00:06:10.783
I shall keep an eye on them.

00:06:12.828 --> 00:06:14.081
C'mon, don't be a weirdo!

00:06:14.164 --> 00:06:16.418
-[door closes]
-Eh, let him do his thing.

00:06:20.260 --> 00:06:22.682
♪

00:06:22.765 --> 00:06:25.688
What could be inside
that mysterious baggage?

00:06:25.771 --> 00:06:28.192
♪

00:06:28.276 --> 00:06:29.444
[gasps]

00:06:32.535 --> 00:06:34.706
[crow cawing]

00:06:34.789 --> 00:06:36.501
Damned corners!

00:06:38.254 --> 00:06:40.300
-[phone rings]
-Uh?

00:06:43.640 --> 00:06:44.934
Uh, hello?

00:06:45.018 --> 00:06:47.355
[ASHIYA] Hello, have I reached
Miss Suzuki's phone?

00:06:47.439 --> 00:06:49.736
Oh! Uh! Hi, Ashiya!

00:06:50.236 --> 00:06:52.575
So, you calling for a reason,
or just to chat?

00:06:52.658 --> 00:06:54.746
[ASHIYA] If you don't mind,
I'd like to ask you

00:06:54.829 --> 00:06:57.250
for a potentially sensitive
piece of information.

00:06:57.333 --> 00:06:59.964
I don't!
Please, feel free to ask away!

00:07:01.300 --> 00:07:04.264
No luck.
They gave me the slip.

00:07:04.347 --> 00:07:06.477
Desperate for information,
I called Miss Suzuki

00:07:06.561 --> 00:07:08.230
to ask if Emilia
had been exhibiting

00:07:08.314 --> 00:07:10.109
any strange behavior
as of late.

00:07:10.193 --> 00:07:12.865
But much like my first mission,
nothing came of it.

00:07:12.948 --> 00:07:15.495
Stalking a group of chicks
wasn't your brightest move.

00:07:15.579 --> 00:07:17.499
But, Sire. The "talk".

00:07:18.209 --> 00:07:20.088
What's worse,
is you probably got

00:07:20.171 --> 00:07:22.467
poor Rika's hopes up
with that call of yours.

00:07:22.551 --> 00:07:23.720
Dumb.

00:07:23.804 --> 00:07:26.726
I'm a big ol' dumb dummy
for expecting anything.

00:07:27.561 --> 00:07:29.732
[EMI]
Alas Ramus! We're back!

00:07:30.483 --> 00:07:32.028
[MAOU]
Hold up. Where's Chi?

00:07:32.112 --> 00:07:33.239
At her place.

00:07:33.322 --> 00:07:36.286
And I walked her all the way
home, so don't even worry.

00:07:36.370 --> 00:07:37.706
-He-he.
-Mama!

00:07:37.790 --> 00:07:40.378
Hey there, sweetie.
Have you been a good girl?

00:07:40.461 --> 00:07:42.967
I watch Angry Bo!
Me and Dada.

00:07:43.552 --> 00:07:45.054
[MAOU] So, where
were you for so long?

00:07:45.138 --> 00:07:45.973
Just around.

00:07:46.056 --> 00:07:48.854
So, your girlish gossip couldn't
be contained in Bel's room?

00:07:48.895 --> 00:07:50.816
It's super musty
in this place.

00:07:50.899 --> 00:07:53.195
Plus, we found
a swanky new pasta shop.

00:07:53.279 --> 00:07:55.116
We've been wanting to try it,
so we did.

00:07:55.199 --> 00:07:56.661
Why, you!

00:07:56.744 --> 00:07:58.372
Must you smear
your exorbitant wealth

00:07:58.455 --> 00:07:59.876
in our faces
at every chance?

00:08:00.209 --> 00:08:01.546
Next time you gorge yourself,

00:08:01.629 --> 00:08:04.176
keep in mind that our dinners
consist of discount cabbage

00:08:04.259 --> 00:08:06.346
paired with verge
-of-expiration pork!

00:08:06.430 --> 00:08:08.768
Purchased at less than one yen a
gram and seasoned with

00:08:08.852 --> 00:08:11.023
but a few sad flakes
of salt and pepper!

00:08:11.106 --> 00:08:13.485
How 'bout we don't
advertise our poverty?

00:08:13.570 --> 00:08:14.822
It's depressing.

00:08:14.906 --> 00:08:18.412
No way Sasazuka's got a pasta
joint you could call swanky.

00:08:18.495 --> 00:08:21.084
Not true! Don't undersell
our glorious town!

00:08:21.168 --> 00:08:22.796
Now tell it that you're sorry!

00:08:22.880 --> 00:08:25.719
[dog barks]

00:08:26.638 --> 00:08:28.767
Emilia's clearly
hiding something.

00:08:28.850 --> 00:08:30.562
But what could be her endgame?

00:08:30.646 --> 00:08:32.858
I don't think
that there's any sinister plot.

00:08:32.942 --> 00:08:35.781
I bet she's just taking
her mind off things.

00:08:35.864 --> 00:08:37.075
What things?

00:08:37.660 --> 00:08:38.912
You remember.

00:08:38.995 --> 00:08:42.335
I doubt that new info Gabriel
gave her is easy to shake off.

00:08:42.962 --> 00:08:44.548
Emilia's daddio?

00:08:44.632 --> 00:08:48.055
Man is alive and kickin'.
All I did was tell her so.

00:08:48.138 --> 00:08:50.936
Taking you down was, like, the
chick's whole mission in life.

00:08:51.019 --> 00:08:52.606
Maybe they're brainstorming.

00:08:52.690 --> 00:08:55.027
Y'know, finding her
a new purpose and crap.

00:08:55.111 --> 00:08:56.614
I wouldn't say it
quite like that,

00:08:56.698 --> 00:08:57.950
but that's what
I'm thinking.

00:08:58.033 --> 00:09:01.373
Well, Chi and I are both
on the first shift tomorrow.

00:09:01.456 --> 00:09:03.712
Maybe she'll spill
me some beans.

00:09:05.047 --> 00:09:07.553
[CHIHO] Thank you for dining
with us, sir!

00:09:08.095 --> 00:09:09.472
Are you feeling okay?

00:09:09.557 --> 00:09:11.769
Sounds like your volume controls
went kablooey.

00:09:11.853 --> 00:09:15.318
Ah! Gosh, was I being too loud?
I didn't know.

00:09:15.777 --> 00:09:19.827
Hey. After we're done here,
do you wanna go talk somewhere?

00:09:19.910 --> 00:09:21.622
You mean like a date? Yeah!

00:09:21.706 --> 00:09:22.833
That sounds fun!

00:09:22.916 --> 00:09:26.298
Though, you kinda caught me
on a busy day.

00:09:26.381 --> 00:09:28.052
Whatcha up to tomorrow?

00:09:28.135 --> 00:09:30.139
If you're free,
maybe we could hang out then.

00:09:30.222 --> 00:09:32.310
I hear there's a new swanky
pasta place.

00:09:32.393 --> 00:09:35.232
We have something neat
like that in Sasazuka?

00:09:35.316 --> 00:09:38.072
Man. I wish I could go,
but I'm busy then, too.

00:09:38.573 --> 00:09:39.575
Mm.

00:09:39.658 --> 00:09:41.829
[bell rings]

00:09:43.374 --> 00:09:44.376
[sighs]

00:09:44.459 --> 00:09:46.046
[ASHIYA]
Surprise, surprise.

00:09:46.129 --> 00:09:49.010
What other mom would hand off
their kid to the literal devil?

00:09:49.094 --> 00:09:50.471
Dada!

00:09:50.555 --> 00:09:52.225
You not bringing Chi
this time?

00:09:52.893 --> 00:09:54.939
We don't hang out
every day, y'know.

00:09:55.022 --> 00:09:57.235
Only two girls are required
for a girl talk,

00:09:57.318 --> 00:09:59.030
so Emilia shall suffice.

00:09:59.907 --> 00:10:02.495
See ya. And try not to drop
the baby, bucko.

00:10:03.748 --> 00:10:04.834
Tail 'em.

00:10:04.917 --> 00:10:06.587
Just leave it to me,
Your Majesty.

00:10:06.671 --> 00:10:08.340
Agent Ashiya at your service.

00:10:08.424 --> 00:10:09.718
-[URUSHIHARA] Dumb plan.
-Hm?

00:10:09.802 --> 00:10:12.725
You've gotta move past this
old school crap, you geezer.

00:10:12.808 --> 00:10:13.810
Ah!

00:10:14.562 --> 00:10:16.733
♪

00:10:16.816 --> 00:10:18.737
This is so overboard.

00:10:18.820 --> 00:10:21.701
I haven't uninstalled the
tracker I used in Nagano yet.

00:10:21.784 --> 00:10:23.495
And if you've got it,
flaunt it, right?

00:10:23.580 --> 00:10:25.124
Flaunt away, Urushihara!

00:10:25.207 --> 00:10:26.961
Does this convince you
that I have value

00:10:27.044 --> 00:10:28.464
and am more than
just a moocher?

00:10:28.548 --> 00:10:30.176
You moochie! Moosh!

00:10:30.259 --> 00:10:31.094
Yeah.

00:10:31.178 --> 00:10:32.346
Ah?

00:10:32.430 --> 00:10:34.392
-Look, they stopped.
-That place.

00:10:35.604 --> 00:10:36.981
[ASHIYA, MAOU]
The bathhouse?

00:10:39.194 --> 00:10:40.989
This is where I
lost them before.

00:10:41.072 --> 00:10:42.868
I assumed that
they had slipped away

00:10:42.951 --> 00:10:44.287
from me down
one of these streets.

00:10:44.370 --> 00:10:46.041
To think that
they were in the bathhouse

00:10:46.124 --> 00:10:47.586
that lies before my very eyes.

00:10:47.669 --> 00:10:49.380
But they don't have any reason
to be sneaky

00:10:49.464 --> 00:10:51.134
about a bathhouse, right?

00:10:51.802 --> 00:10:55.852
Time to kick back, relax,
and blow some money on Jungle.

00:10:55.936 --> 00:10:57.564
Moochy! Moo!

00:10:57.648 --> 00:10:59.735
You ain't seen anything yet,
baby face.

00:10:59.818 --> 00:11:02.240
I'm gonna teach you
what real moochin' looks like.

00:11:02.323 --> 00:11:03.993
-[bell rings]
-[BOTH] Hm?

00:11:07.543 --> 00:11:08.962
-[electricity zaps]
-[both groan]

00:11:09.045 --> 00:11:11.007
-My lord! It seems--
-Yeah.

00:11:11.091 --> 00:11:12.594
They put up a legit barrier.

00:11:12.678 --> 00:11:14.849
[phone rings]

00:11:14.932 --> 00:11:16.393
This better be good!

00:11:16.476 --> 00:11:18.313
[URUSHIHARA] Don't freak,
but we've got trouble.

00:11:18.397 --> 00:11:21.069
It's a message.
Straight from the land lady.

00:11:21.152 --> 00:11:23.031
[groans]

00:11:24.284 --> 00:11:27.708
[URUSHIHARA] It's not just a
tape this time. We've got a DVD.

00:11:31.674 --> 00:11:33.427
Our first digital screening.

00:11:33.511 --> 00:11:35.180
This should be a joyous
occasion.

00:11:35.264 --> 00:11:37.143
Why do I feel so
racked with fear?

00:11:37.226 --> 00:11:39.147
Come on, man. You know why.

00:11:40.984 --> 00:11:42.779
[all gasping]

00:11:43.488 --> 00:11:45.660
[birds chirping]

00:11:45.744 --> 00:11:48.248
-Is that...
-The Amazon?

00:11:48.332 --> 00:11:49.668
Why the Amazon?

00:11:49.752 --> 00:11:50.962
Hello there, boys.

00:11:51.046 --> 00:11:52.883
I hope you darlings
are doing well.

00:11:52.966 --> 00:11:56.724
I'm terribly sorry that job
I sent you off on fell through.

00:11:56.807 --> 00:11:58.519
My niece's schedule
got in the way,

00:11:58.603 --> 00:12:00.481
but I'm sure you young people
relate to the--

00:12:00.565 --> 00:12:02.109
Wait, who's her niece?

00:12:02.193 --> 00:12:03.655
Miss Amane, dude.

00:12:04.197 --> 00:12:05.950
You know, from the
beach in Choshi?

00:12:06.493 --> 00:12:08.205
Right. Now it's coming back.

00:12:08.288 --> 00:12:11.252
This might not make up
for that awful inconvenience,

00:12:11.336 --> 00:12:13.591
but would you strapping young
men be so kind

00:12:13.675 --> 00:12:15.344
as to weed the backyard for me?

00:12:15.427 --> 00:12:16.639
This will be your payment.

00:12:16.722 --> 00:12:19.394
If you're willing, I'll deduct
it directly from your rent.

00:12:19.477 --> 00:12:21.941
Thank you in
advance, my darlings.

00:12:22.776 --> 00:12:25.030
[ASHIYA] I appreciate
the fifteen-thousand yen, but...

00:12:25.114 --> 00:12:28.453
[MAOU] She paused an Amazonian
expedition to ask for lawn care?

00:12:28.538 --> 00:12:31.292
[URUSHIHARA] I'm just glad
this video was safe for work.

00:12:31.376 --> 00:12:34.048
So, she wants us to weed?

00:12:34.132 --> 00:12:35.300
[gasps]

00:12:35.384 --> 00:12:37.848
Perfect! We can use this!

00:12:37.931 --> 00:12:39.058
Hm?

00:12:39.142 --> 00:12:42.148
♪

00:12:45.905 --> 00:12:47.659
Screw this sun.

00:12:47.743 --> 00:12:50.456
I agreed to some light weeding,
not melting to death.

00:12:50.540 --> 00:12:53.588
I'll admit, this is harder labor
than I anticipated.

00:12:53.671 --> 00:12:56.217
I feel awful that you got stuck
helping us, Chi.

00:12:56.342 --> 00:12:57.303
It's okay.

00:12:57.386 --> 00:13:00.184
I'm always down to help you
guys, that's why I offered!

00:13:00.267 --> 00:13:01.812
Thanks for your skills, Suz.

00:13:01.896 --> 00:13:04.735
Environmental tidiness
falls on the whole community.

00:13:04.818 --> 00:13:06.572
[ALAS RAMUS]
Dada!

00:13:06.655 --> 00:13:08.408
[giggles]

00:13:08.492 --> 00:13:10.245
Hey! Look who it is!

00:13:10.329 --> 00:13:11.999
Oh, hi! What's up?

00:13:12.082 --> 00:13:13.168
What's up with you?

00:13:13.251 --> 00:13:15.005
You know it's boiling
out here, right?

00:13:15.089 --> 00:13:16.592
Dost thou have eyes?

00:13:16.675 --> 00:13:17.844
We're weeding!

00:13:17.928 --> 00:13:20.015
It seems we finished
just in time.

00:13:20.098 --> 00:13:21.811
We ready to go, girls?

00:13:21.894 --> 00:13:23.731
I guess we should
get going, too.

00:13:23.815 --> 00:13:25.652
Uh? You're leaving?

00:13:25.735 --> 00:13:26.737
Yeah.

00:13:26.821 --> 00:13:28.783
We're gonna clean up
at the bath house.

00:13:29.242 --> 00:13:30.244
[gasps]

00:13:32.498 --> 00:13:33.500
Crazy!

00:13:33.584 --> 00:13:35.087
You were planning a bath, too?

00:13:35.170 --> 00:13:36.924
What a hilarious coincidence!

00:13:37.007 --> 00:13:38.761
Maybe we should skip today.

00:13:38.845 --> 00:13:40.389
We can't go on this way.

00:13:40.472 --> 00:13:43.353
We've stretched the wool far too
thin to pull over their eyes.

00:13:43.436 --> 00:13:44.982
Hey, what is that
supposed to mean?

00:13:45.065 --> 00:13:47.152
Uh, just girl talk stuff.

00:13:47.236 --> 00:13:49.658
Mama and Dada! With me!

00:13:49.741 --> 00:13:51.996
Hey, don't get the wrong idea,
cutie patootie.

00:13:52.079 --> 00:13:54.751
Mama and Dada can't bathe
together with you.

00:13:57.131 --> 00:13:58.593
Three adults, please.

00:13:58.676 --> 00:14:00.012
[TOYO] Yes, ma'am.

00:14:00.095 --> 00:14:02.391
-Thanks.
-Dada too!

00:14:02.474 --> 00:14:05.648
Sorry, hun. Dadas aren't allowed
on this side.

00:14:05.732 --> 00:14:07.109
A moment, Maou.

00:14:07.192 --> 00:14:08.821
Of course. What's up?

00:14:08.905 --> 00:14:10.240
That your wife?

00:14:10.867 --> 00:14:13.246
You could say
she's my baby mama.

00:14:13.789 --> 00:14:15.250
Mm.

00:14:16.461 --> 00:14:18.256
We're the first
folks here again!

00:14:18.340 --> 00:14:19.509
Perfect.

00:14:19.635 --> 00:14:21.220
It's training time, girls.

00:14:21.304 --> 00:14:22.974
Choo-choo!

00:14:23.058 --> 00:14:25.855
Yay! I'm ready
to do this thing!

00:14:26.481 --> 00:14:27.609
Training?

00:14:27.692 --> 00:14:30.113
It sounds like it,
but for what?

00:14:33.078 --> 00:14:37.127
♪

00:14:40.677 --> 00:14:42.681
[SUZUNO]
To begin, drink this.

00:14:42.764 --> 00:14:43.975
'Kay!

00:14:45.185 --> 00:14:46.855
What do you think
she's drinking?

00:14:46.939 --> 00:14:49.402
Ooh! Perhaps that
coffee-flavored milk!

00:14:49.485 --> 00:14:51.699
Bringing in outside drinks
is a big no-no!

00:14:51.782 --> 00:14:53.744
Damn, not a no-no.

00:14:53.828 --> 00:14:57.251
That and, what training
requires coffee-flavored milk?

00:14:57.334 --> 00:14:59.881
-MgCafé!
-I think not.

00:15:03.221 --> 00:15:05.935
-Heavens.
-They always get me.

00:15:06.019 --> 00:15:09.150
[SUZUNO] Uh! How can our
compositions be so different?

00:15:09.233 --> 00:15:10.945
My nutrition is just as good.

00:15:11.029 --> 00:15:12.741
[EMI] Think about it
for a second, Bel!

00:15:12.824 --> 00:15:14.828
Those things would be
a huge nuisance in battle.

00:15:14.911 --> 00:15:15.913
[SUZUNO] You're right.

00:15:15.997 --> 00:15:18.544
Noncombatants can afford
such luxuries.

00:15:18.627 --> 00:15:20.297
Noncombatants what?

00:15:20.380 --> 00:15:23.261
-A nuisance in battle?
-I'm big-time lost.

00:15:24.388 --> 00:15:25.516
[sighs]

00:15:25.600 --> 00:15:27.562
-[bell ringing]
-[CHIHO] Is something wrong?

00:15:27.645 --> 00:15:29.733
Look in the mirror
and take a guess.

00:15:29.816 --> 00:15:31.027
Hm?

00:15:31.653 --> 00:15:34.283
It's not a concern.
Let us proceed.

00:15:36.496 --> 00:15:38.876
Your vital signs
appear to be stable.

00:15:38.959 --> 00:15:41.799
-Any changes in your condition?
-Nuh-uh!

00:15:41.882 --> 00:15:45.263
No need to be nervous.
Just relax and breathe normally.

00:15:45.347 --> 00:15:47.519
That's why we're at the bath,
after all.

00:15:47.602 --> 00:15:49.063
It's time to begin.

00:15:49.146 --> 00:15:50.858
We'll start with
waterfall training.

00:15:50.942 --> 00:15:52.779
Waterfall!

00:15:52.862 --> 00:15:55.283
Waterfall training
for a MgCafé job?

00:15:55.367 --> 00:15:57.872
I'm telling you,
this isn't about MgCafé.

00:15:57.956 --> 00:16:01.087
Who cares? How could they even
do that in a bathhouse?

00:16:01.839 --> 00:16:03.341
I have your answer, Sire.

00:16:03.424 --> 00:16:05.387
-[MAOU] Hm?
-With those!

00:16:05.470 --> 00:16:10.147
♪

00:16:15.825 --> 00:16:17.035
All right.

00:16:17.119 --> 00:16:18.747
That should be plenty for now.

00:16:18.831 --> 00:16:21.085
Next, you'll need to get
into a lukewarm bath.

00:16:21.169 --> 00:16:22.045
[CHIHO]
Right!

00:16:22.129 --> 00:16:24.551
♪

00:16:24.634 --> 00:16:25.678
[EMI]
Nice.

00:16:25.761 --> 00:16:28.016
Relax, and put your focus
onto that little spot

00:16:28.099 --> 00:16:30.521
where the water from the shower
was hitting your head.

00:16:30.605 --> 00:16:33.067
Imagine a celestial force
starting there,

00:16:33.151 --> 00:16:36.032
and flowing through your body
to the tips of your toes.

00:16:36.617 --> 00:16:39.623
[groaning softly]

00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:42.085
Good.

00:16:42.169 --> 00:16:45.258
You're doing well.
Now open your eyes and sit up.

00:16:45.718 --> 00:16:48.515
This is when I do that thing
we worked on, right?

00:16:48.891 --> 00:16:50.018
That's correct.

00:16:50.101 --> 00:16:52.272
Our techniques give form
to a mental image.

00:16:52.356 --> 00:16:53.399
Though, trust me.

00:16:53.483 --> 00:16:55.362
I know the activation of
celestial force

00:16:55.445 --> 00:16:57.115
can be difficult
to imagine.

00:16:57.199 --> 00:16:58.869
Thus, we vocalize.

00:16:58.953 --> 00:17:00.915
Like how Bel says,
"Light of Iron".

00:17:00.998 --> 00:17:03.336
Or like how I say,
"Divine Boots of Light".

00:17:03.419 --> 00:17:06.008
To make your image concrete,
just say it out loud!

00:17:06.092 --> 00:17:09.056
Jeez. What's the big deal
with this celestial force crap?

00:17:09.139 --> 00:17:11.561
All you could use in here is
"Divine Towel".

00:17:11.645 --> 00:17:13.774
Bloodbath was bathhouse, huh?

00:17:13.857 --> 00:17:16.571
-That's it, I'm going in.
-I warn you against it, Sire!

00:17:16.655 --> 00:17:18.909
Take one naked step
onto the female's territory,

00:17:18.993 --> 00:17:20.788
and the police will
be called at once!

00:17:20.871 --> 00:17:23.376
Don't think it matters
if his step is naked or not.

00:17:23.459 --> 00:17:25.088
-[MAOU] Get off me, Ashiya!
-It's for the best, Sire!

00:17:25.171 --> 00:17:26.758
No need to worry,
Good Chiho.

00:17:26.842 --> 00:17:28.595
-They can't do anything here.
-[MAOU] No more spy crap--

00:17:28.679 --> 00:17:30.307
Not so long
as we're in the women's bath.

00:17:30.390 --> 00:17:32.436
I put up a strong barrier.

00:17:32.520 --> 00:17:34.607
I can make sure the front desk
alady is still asleep

00:17:34.691 --> 00:17:36.611
if that'll make you
feel better.

00:17:37.572 --> 00:17:39.408
Cry out with all your might.

00:17:40.035 --> 00:17:43.249
Since you're merely activating
the force, any words will do.

00:17:43.333 --> 00:17:45.086
Shout them
with your full chest.

00:17:45.170 --> 00:17:46.882
Release them out
into the world.

00:17:46.965 --> 00:17:49.763
But, what if Mister Maou
can hear me yelling?

00:17:49.846 --> 00:17:52.225
Overcoming humiliation
greatly intensifies

00:17:52.309 --> 00:17:53.687
psychological release.

00:17:53.812 --> 00:17:56.192
With Maou just beyond that wall,
I suspect

00:17:56.275 --> 00:17:59.616
our training session today will
be more effective than usual.

00:18:00.241 --> 00:18:02.914
Ah! Huh?

00:18:06.295 --> 00:18:07.548
[Chiho yelling]

00:18:07.632 --> 00:18:08.759
Crap! That's Chi!

00:18:08.842 --> 00:18:11.263
I'm begging you
to come to your senses, my lord!

00:18:11.347 --> 00:18:12.391
Get caught,
and you'll be branded

00:18:12.474 --> 00:18:14.144
a pervert
the rest of your days!

00:18:14.228 --> 00:18:17.275
[grunts] Well, in that case...
Moocher! Get over there!

00:18:17.359 --> 00:18:19.614
You better quit acting like
I'm the obvious candidate

00:18:19.698 --> 00:18:20.908
for pervert-hood around here!

00:18:20.991 --> 00:18:22.662
[yelling]

00:18:22.745 --> 00:18:24.916
Let it bellow from your soul!

00:18:24.999 --> 00:18:26.962
[Chiho yelling]

00:18:27.045 --> 00:18:28.632
[SUZUNO]
Good, that's the spirit!

00:18:28.715 --> 00:18:31.429
-[MAOU] Pipe down!
-[ALAS RAMUS] Dada!

00:18:31.470 --> 00:18:33.726
Aw, come on, baby
girl, not you, too!

00:18:33.809 --> 00:18:35.019
[Chiho yelling]

00:18:35.103 --> 00:18:36.480
Make them stop, Emi!

00:18:36.565 --> 00:18:37.734
I don't know
what you're up to,

00:18:37.817 --> 00:18:39.904
but I can't tolerate disturbers
of the peace!

00:18:39.988 --> 00:18:42.159
[EMI] I'll explain later,
just ignore it, okay?

00:18:42.242 --> 00:18:44.413
[CHIHO] May I take your order,
ma'am?

00:18:44.496 --> 00:18:45.875
[SUZUNO] One MgDouble,
extra loud!

00:18:45.958 --> 00:18:47.127
-This has gone too far!
-[ALAS RAMUS] Dada!

00:18:47.210 --> 00:18:49.381
Keep MgDouble's name
out your mouth!

00:18:49.799 --> 00:18:51.177
Wait! My lord!

00:18:51.970 --> 00:18:54.475
Ahh!

00:18:54.976 --> 00:18:56.103
[grunts]

00:18:56.187 --> 00:18:57.565
[MAOU] Emi!

00:18:57.690 --> 00:19:00.278
Fess up, what the hell
are you two doing to Chi?

00:19:00.361 --> 00:19:01.489
You can't tell?

00:19:02.575 --> 00:19:05.413
Technically speaking,
I guess we didn't use that much.

00:19:05.497 --> 00:19:06.750
Much what?

00:19:06.833 --> 00:19:08.879
You're shooting
yourself in the foot.

00:19:08.962 --> 00:19:11.342
It might be fun and games
right now, but next time

00:19:11.425 --> 00:19:12.970
there's a battle,
you're gonna waste forces

00:19:13.054 --> 00:19:14.891
protecting a soldier
who can't fight.

00:19:14.974 --> 00:19:17.270
Good grief,
of course, we're not.

00:19:17.354 --> 00:19:19.191
And Chiho knows that,
trust me.

00:19:19.274 --> 00:19:20.945
This whole thing
was her idea.

00:19:21.028 --> 00:19:22.823
She just wants
the ability to warn us

00:19:22.907 --> 00:19:25.663
if she finds herself
in an emergency situation.

00:19:25.746 --> 00:19:28.251
Warn us, huh? You mean...

00:19:28.334 --> 00:19:30.129
[EMI] Yeah. Idea linking.

00:19:31.131 --> 00:19:32.425
When Sariel kidnapped her,

00:19:32.510 --> 00:19:35.683
he took her phone so she would
be completely cut off from us.

00:19:35.766 --> 00:19:36.935
It makes sense.

00:19:37.728 --> 00:19:39.064
So, Chi.

00:19:39.147 --> 00:19:41.151
If a crisis like
that happens again,

00:19:41.235 --> 00:19:44.324
she doesn't want to cause you
any more trouble than necessary.

00:19:44.408 --> 00:19:46.370
She's doing all
this to help you.

00:19:47.122 --> 00:19:49.711
Please know, the good Chiho
spent several days

00:19:49.794 --> 00:19:52.007
thinking over this path
before proceeding.

00:19:52.090 --> 00:19:53.134
[ALAS]
All done yelling?

00:19:53.217 --> 00:19:55.598
I ask that you
respect her wishes.

00:19:55.681 --> 00:19:58.854
I just want to help.

00:19:58.937 --> 00:20:00.231
Yeah, I know.

00:20:00.315 --> 00:20:03.112
When this blows
up, I told ya so.

00:20:03.195 --> 00:20:05.241
You want this?
You're sure?

00:20:07.580 --> 00:20:12.047
Yeah, 'cause now, I won't get
in your way or drag you down.

00:20:12.130 --> 00:20:14.719
Not as much as I
have before, anyway.

00:20:15.679 --> 00:20:18.225
I need to make sure
I can always escape.

00:20:18.309 --> 00:20:20.271
And if I can't,
then at the very least,

00:20:20.355 --> 00:20:22.652
I'll be able to help
you guys help me.

00:20:22.735 --> 00:20:23.987
[ALAS]
Uh-oh!

00:20:24.530 --> 00:20:25.574
Come on, Chi.

00:20:25.658 --> 00:20:27.536
We're monsters
from another world.

00:20:27.703 --> 00:20:30.041
You can leave all the
responsibility to us.

00:20:30.124 --> 00:20:32.797
Besides, we got you mixed up
in this great big mess.

00:20:32.880 --> 00:20:34.884
So, it's our job
to pull you out.

00:20:34.967 --> 00:20:37.598
She's not the type
to let you carry her burden.

00:20:37.682 --> 00:20:39.769
Especially since
there's a way to lighten it.

00:20:39.852 --> 00:20:42.232
She doesn't want power
so she can leap into danger,

00:20:42.315 --> 00:20:43.860
but to stay safe for us.

00:20:44.737 --> 00:20:46.240
I find that very touching.

00:20:49.287 --> 00:20:51.876
[CHIHO] Thank you very,
very much for today.

00:20:52.335 --> 00:20:54.507
[EMI] You'll get some practical
experience next time.

00:20:55.216 --> 00:20:57.053
-I, uh...
-Hm?

00:20:57.137 --> 00:20:58.682
Have something to report!

00:20:58.849 --> 00:21:00.811
Or, um, it's just
possibly something

00:21:00.894 --> 00:21:03.023
that I really think
you ought to know about.

00:21:03.107 --> 00:21:05.654
Well, whatever it is,
report away, private.

00:21:05.738 --> 00:21:10.163
It's just... Whoever it was
that was living inside my body?

00:21:10.246 --> 00:21:12.167
They left some
memories behind.

00:21:14.254 --> 00:21:17.218
I have this clear
image of a big man.

00:21:17.302 --> 00:21:19.264
He seems like a nice,
middle-aged guy

00:21:19.347 --> 00:21:21.519
with a beard
and a short-ish ponytail.

00:21:21.603 --> 00:21:24.399
-He's in a golden field.
-A what?

00:21:24.483 --> 00:21:25.694
[CHIHO]
Of rice?

00:21:25.944 --> 00:21:30.078
Is there any chance that golden
field might actually be wheat?

00:21:30.161 --> 00:21:31.915
I suppose it could be.

00:21:31.998 --> 00:21:33.794
The man speaks to me, too.

00:21:33.877 --> 00:21:36.591
Even though he
only says one word.

00:21:36.674 --> 00:21:38.385
"Aciethalla".

00:21:38.929 --> 00:21:40.891
"Aciethalla?"

00:21:40.974 --> 00:21:43.270
Does that mean anything
special to you?

00:21:43.354 --> 00:21:45.651
No. I'm sorry.

00:21:45.818 --> 00:21:47.153
It doesn't.

00:21:47.237 --> 00:21:48.949
♪

00:21:49.032 --> 00:21:52.247
But if you really have
such a vivid memory of that man,

00:21:52.706 --> 00:21:55.086
the person in your body
had to have been...

00:21:55.169 --> 00:21:58.175
♪

00:21:59.469 --> 00:22:01.850
It's late. What's wrong?

00:22:01.933 --> 00:22:03.143
Nothing much.

00:22:04.647 --> 00:22:07.235
We made the right call,
didn't we?

00:22:07.360 --> 00:22:10.366
♪

